---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Headline from '../components/Headline.astro';
import Paragraph from '../components/Paragraph.astro';
import CodeBlock from '../components/CodeBlock.astro';
import Badge from '../components/Badge.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  seoTitle="BaseLayout & Accessible Fonts"
  seoDescription="A minimal scaffold for WCAG-compliant pages and prop-based selection of accessible fonts."
  containerSize="lg"
>
  <div slot="header">
    <header class="mb-6">
      <Headline level="h1" textSize="2xl" weight="extrabold"
        >BaseLayout & Accessible Fonts</Headline
      >
    </header>
  </div>

  <div slot="main">
    <section class="space-y-8">
      <Paragraph size="md" variant="muted" maxWidth="prose">
        The <code>BaseLayout</code> provides a minimal, semantic scaffold including
        landmarks, a skip link, a header, optional sidebar and footer. It ensures
        basic WCAG practices (structure, focus, contrast) are present by default.
      </Paragraph>

      <Headline level="h2" textSize="lg" weight="bold">Props</Headline>
      <div class="space-y-4 text-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="seoTitle" variant="neutral" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >SEO page title (string; used for the &lt;title&gt; tag)</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="seoDescription" variant="neutral" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Meta description (for SEO)</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="lang" variant="neutral" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Language code (default: en)</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="fontMode" variant="accent" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Accessible font choices: <code
              >default | atkinson | opendyslexic</code
            ></span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="highLegibility" variant="success" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Enable high legibility (larger line-height and word-spacing)</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="heading" variant="neutral" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Optional H1 provided directly by the layout</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="containerSize" variant="neutral" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Container width: sm | md | lg | xl | 2xl | full</span
          >
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2 items-center">
          <Badge label="announceRegion" variant="neutral" />
          <span class="text-slate-600 dark:text-slate-400"
            >Enable screen reader live region</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>

      <Headline level="h2" textSize="lg" weight="bold">Example</Headline>
      <CodeBlock lang="astro">
        {
          `---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  seoTitle="Home"
  seoDescription="Demo using Atkinson Hyperlegible"
  fontMode="atkinson"
  highLegibility={true}
  heading="Welcome"
  containerSize="lg"
>
  <p>This page uses Atkinson Hyperlegible for improved readability.</p>
</BaseLayout>`
        }
      </CodeBlock>

      <Headline level="h2" textSize="lg" weight="bold">Fonts & Notes</Headline>
      <ul
        class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-sm text-slate-700 dark:text-slate-300"
      >
        <li>
          <strong>Atkinson Hyperlegible:</strong> Optimized for visual impairments
          (distinct letterforms).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>OpenDyslexic:</strong> Open-source font with heavier bottoms to
          anchor letter shapes.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Other specialty fonts:</strong> A number of licensed or specialty
          fonts exist, but they are not included in the default set and may require
          separate licensing and hosting.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Monospace fonts:</strong> Use monospaced fonts for code blocks
          only (avoid using them as the primary body font).
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Performance:</strong> In production host local <code
            >@font-face</code
          > files and use preload.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Color & contrast testing:</strong> Changing fonts can cause minor
          pixel shifts â€” run visual regression tests.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <Headline level="h2" textSize="lg" weight="bold">Best Practices</Headline>
      <Paragraph size="sm" variant="muted" maxWidth="prose">
        Use <code>fontMode</code> sparingly per page. Consider a global user font
        preference toggle to respect user choices. For dyslexia-optimized fonts,
        also prefer moderate line lengths (~72ch) and sufficient line spacing.
      </Paragraph>
    </section>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
